outputs.output_descr:
This project provides support to the following:
1) Economic development activities and skills training of youth and women;  
2) UN support to development of a facilitatory regulatory environment and support strengthening of national statistics and M&E systems;
3) Support private sector development activities; 
4) Development of key development reports [MDGR, NHDR, and Quarterly Socio-economic Reviews]; and
4) Support the mainstreaming of HIV/AIDs and Gender into programmatic areas based on evidence based research. 

Special efforts will be made towards  encouraging women and youth entrepreneurship activities through appropriate skills training, business advisory services and development of value chains, to encourage greater production and consequent economic growth.This will be complemented by activities for private sector development.  Support to development of investment and related policies and advocating for MDG acceleration and discussions on Post 2015 will also be undertaken. Underpinning these activities the issues of HIV/AIDS and Gender mainstreaming would also be taken up.
